<ProseLayout 
  title="About Phronos"
  description="An observatory for human cognition in the era of artificial intelligence"
>
  <h2>What Phronos Is</h2>
  <p>A think tank and a cognitive clinic in one.</p>
  <p>
    Phronos is an observatory for human cognition—a place of structured observation 
    rather than instruction. We develop ways to measure how you think, and we 
    communicate our observations to show you how your thinking compares to the 
    machines thinking alongside you.
  </p>

  <h2>The Founder</h2>
  <div class="founder-block">
    <div class="founder-avatar">VP</div>
    <div class="founder-info">
      <p class="founder-name">Vishal Patel</p>
      <p class="founder-credentials">MD · PhD (Genetics)</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <blockquote>
    <p>
      "What I think about most is how people think: how do we know what we know? 
      How do we believe what we believe?"
    </p>
  </blockquote>

  <h2>The Work</h2>
  <p>
    Phronos serves as a trusted observatory for global human cognition—delivering 
    open-source frameworks grounded in science, instruments that reveal how we think 
    in relation to machines, and a commons where individual insight produces 
    collective understanding.
  </p>
  <p>The observatory produces four kinds of output:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dispatches</strong> — Essays that report what the observatory detects</li>
    <li><strong>Methods</strong> — Methodologies for measuring cognition, published openly</li>
    <li><strong>Instruments</strong> — Tools for measuring cognition</li>
    <li><strong>Data</strong> — A commons of anonymized observations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The Question</h2>
  <p>
    The defining question of this era is not <em>who am I?</em> but 
    <em>where am I still myself?</em>
  </p>
  <p>
    Our cognition is being actively reshaped by our information environment, but we 
    lack objective, practical measures to inform our fitness. Meanwhile, a new 
    intelligence has entered the world. It learns from us, speaks like us, and 
    thinks alongside us.
  </p>

